caption: (Translated by Google) Very good combos  (Original) Muy buenos los combos
Delicious japchae!
We missed Korean food during Covid. No more. Delivery was prompt and FOOD IS GREAT!  Especially Pork Ssam and Korean Tacos.
A hidden gem! Best korean spot in fort greene. The owner is super sweet, a badass woman 🕺🏻
Amazing food!
This place constantly delivers. They have awesome dishes for reasonable rates, there no long wait even when they are full.

This site is my preferable place.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to that place. Whenever  I want to go to a special supper, this is the place that comes straight to my head. splendid and varied  food and a rich menu.generous staff, and great ambience. Also important, the cost is reasonable. I tell about this place with no hesitation.
The place offers a fantastic range of fresh food. I liked dining here. The employees are always friendly, pricing is fair and the spot is always well organised.

Ordered the japchae dosirak on seamless, and this is legit some of the best Korean food I've had in Brooklyn! I love the chefs choice banchan ((side dishes)), and the kimchi is out of this world! Will definitely be ordering here A LOT, thank you!!!
Good food. Nice staff. Owner very friendly
They offer a large variety of fresh food. I loved dining here. Staff members are always very friendly, prices are reasonable and the spot is always neat.

Tiger Box serves tasty, affordable Korean food, chock full of delicious veggies. I did pick up and the  staff was super kind and my order was on time. I absolutely recommend the seafood paijun pancake. The soondoubu was delicious (excellent tofu, mild spicy broth, flooooofy rice). The galbi over kimchi fried rice was super and we enjoyed all the different components of a well made bimbimbap. Food is more homestyle than KTown and I appreciated that everything had a balanced flavor vs overly sweet or salty. We will be back!
This has been the biggest surprise of our shelter in place food deliveries.  Everything we had was DELICIOUS.  Didn't know what to expect but we'll definitely be ordering again.

I sent my friends to this place with my warmest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The the food there is flavorable and the team is very friendly and cooperative. Whenever we visit this place we pass a pleasant time.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
Simply amazing food ! Always leaves me wanting more . Bulgogi Bibimbop delicious & let's not forget the fantastic taco's.  Yummy yummy yummy !

I ordered on Seamless, order took a little longer so the food arrived a slightly cold, but it was not the restaurants fault but the delivery driver taking a longer route. Even though it was cold, it was still delicious! Only objectives would be that more dipping sauce was needed for the Mandoo, barely any in the ramekin, enough for two dumplings. Also, the Pajeon could have been a bit crisper, but the flavors in both were great and the Bulgogi Taco was amazing! Perhaps you can have an individual add on cause I could have eaten 4!!! Thank you, will order again.. Never knew about this place!
I visit this place a lot since I work close by. I love how their customer service is always excellent and they keep the place clean constantly
Amazing food! Good place is you’re looking for a cozy homemade Korean meal!
Tiger box is a great place to order great korean food!
I was craving a homey Korean place that isn't so "westernized" this place hits the spot

Food is very good, price is not bad. Location seems kind of out of the way, but great for take-out and if you go in, there is a small eating area, it's very nice. A great option if you want somewhere to eat and you are working in the Brooklyn Navy Yard. The owner is super nice! I think they need more volume for deliveries, but this place would do great if they did have delivery, based on the location. Lunch delivery to the navy yard. Dinner delivery up the hill. Anyway, I like this place I recommend checking it out.
This is a hidden gem tucked away under the BQE. All food is prepared to order by the owner/cook who was very friendly. The japchae box was delicious and inexpensive. I will be back!
Really great service and amazing food! Definitely recommend trying the Spicy Pork Bowl!!
Love the spicy pork bowl!
I always arrive purchasing some food in this place. I liked the rapid service and well cooked food. Fantastic work.
Delicious. Had the Galbi Box. Was not disappointed.

They have a great selection and a large variety of cuisines. A taste array of Korean dishes. We had bibimbap combo with steamed japchae dumplings, Bulgogi, and Veggie Tofu Fritters, and I recommend you to try. Delicious and price were right for the quality. Service was attentive. Overall, a good experience.

Good casual Korean food. The Lady making the food is very nice and attentive. The self check-out is okay to use and my sense is they do a lot of delivery here. I had a beef bowl and it tasted good with plenty of veggies and a side of kimchi. Parking is never an issue with spots right in front and across the street.
Woman inside with glasses has some serious look and ignored customers. she has bad vibes to make their business look bad.
It's was ok. People were super nice.  Food was nothing special.
I ordered this soup for delivery, it came with no pork, no onions, no green scallions at all.... only a little bit big tofus and many many many kimchi.... full of kimchi. Won’t order again.
Awesome visit. Nice food and fair prices, but the owner was the real gem. Great atmosphere for a quick bite. The spicy pork bowl was very good.

Great cozy Korean food spot.  Nestled under the BQE, in a gritty hard-scrabble area, the food transports you to a otherworldly.The owners are warm and inviting, a welcome antidote to harsh realities and coarse attitudes of everyday New Yorkers.  Be sure to visit.
Friendly staff, food comes very quickly, it's always good, I especially recommend the Bibimbap and the Kimbap. Never had a bad experience here, the food's always a good price and delicious!
Good home made taste but way over priced these dishes would be so cheap in Korea

I arrive at this superb restaurant every couple of days since I enjoy the  special atmosphere that is exist in this restaurant. The crew is extraordianrillyremarkably helpful and qualified. The service is exceptionally rapid. Also, the food they serve is first-rate. I visited many times and I was always happy. The price is modest. I highly recommend this restaurant to my friends and family.
Feel not so well after having the scallions seafood pancake...
The food is outstanding! Especially for the take out place!
Had a awesome experience in this spot with my kid. The food comes out fast and the customer service is just good. Prices are affordable.
Tried this spot once with a friend and I am addicted ever since. I love the great atmosphere and tasty food and beverages. Keep up the good work.

Very randomly I had lunch here today, it was simply such a wonderful surprise and treat!!! So delicious and fresh I wish I lived close enough to come 3 or 4 times a week. The owner came and we chatted for a little while, so welcoming and warm. If you live in the neighborhood be sure to check it out and tell your friends. Truly a gem!!!  I will definitely be back :))
Awesome spot to buy some food when in a rush. The service is fast, prices are fair, excellent character. I highly recommend this spot.
So friendly, great food for a great price!
I had the Veggie Bibimbop and it was delicious. Also the people were supernice and helpful
This place knows how to take care of their customers. Constantly with a very kind attitude. The food is fairly priced, regularly flavorful and neat.
Fresh, authentic Korean food, run by good people.
The food was fantastic, everything is cooked fresh to order. Try the kimchi combo delicious.
Tiger Box has been my go-to for lunch in the Brooklyn Navy Yard. Friendly service and delicious food at a reasonable price!
Best Korean comfort food in the Fort Greene/Clinton Hill area! The scallion pancakes are my fave. I would upload a photo but I already scarfed it down.
I love this spot! The food is delicious and consistently so. The mandoo (dumplings) are fantastic. And the owner is so nice!
Lady is very friendly, food is very tasty and I encourage you to order from here. Never disappoints.
Good Korean food 🥘 I really enjoy it
Really good food  the menu for you to have a many different kind of food
Spicy pork and Bulgogi Bibimbap.  Do it.  It's small (one table)  but they are super friendly and quick.
Amazing food and such great service! New fav

The food is delicious, can’t be beat. The customer service leaves much to be desired however. They’re delivery orders are often late or to the wrong address, they’ve forgotten extra sauces we requested and are unhelpful over the phone.  But the food is so phenomenal that we keep coming back!  I’d suggest just avoiding delivery, and going in to the location for better service. Unfortunately we live to far away for that option.
Very friendly and tasty

My husband and I have tried nearly every Korean restaurant in Brooklyn because we got obsessed with bibimbap. Despite the fact that this is mostly a take out spot, Tiger Box is now our favorite place.  Sain, the owner,  consistently makes  the  highest quality, most flavorful  bibimbap with lots of delicious vegetables and a leaf vegetable she imports directly from Korea.  Despite its locale,  we couldn't recommend this spot more strongly.
Weird location. Super yummy. Very nice staff.

Have tried Tiger Box twice and after the second time wondered why i don't eat their food more often. Affordable healthy food that tastes amazing. As others stated I wish they were open every evening. No doubt in my mind I'd be a regular if store hours extended into the evening on most days.

The food is delicious! I got the lunch taco special and enjoyed it. The food was fresh and had a nice balance of flavors. The prices are comparable to most similar places in the area, and the wait was very short despite going during prime lunch hours. I kinda wish the tacos came with something small on the side, but I'll be going back when the mood strikes.
Fantastic quality and flavor plus the owner is incredibly nice
There is an A on the front door for good reason...Great food...Gotta try it.....
Please open for more nights!

Friendly, tasty, and quick! I've been wanting a quick Korean takeout spot near my work forever. I got the bulgogi (beef) bibimbop and it was great! It was pretty empty and I was able to eat it they're, at their one medium sized table. The owner/chef, Sai (not sure of spelling) talked to me and answered my questions and was extremely nice. Will be back soon!
Tasty, fresh, lovely food..!
Delicious, inexpensive and quick.Take-out with 1 long table, 2 benches, 2 stools. The bathroom contains a defunct bathtub - classic NYC.
Food is good but it takes a while to cook.
Eaten here 3 times, everything is fantastic!
